<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?><?Xpress productLine="ncc-clause" ?><clause author="Brandon Kiem" dateTime="2021-03-12T08:28:17" id="_a6311458-a7ed-4726-9e5b-2c1b96c82dc1" outputclass="ncc-clause" type="insert"><meta><facet building="Class 2"/><facet building="Class 3"/><facet building="Class 4"/><facet building="Class 5"/><facet building="Class 6"/><facet building="Class 7a"/><facet building="Class 7b"/><facet building="Class 8"/><facet building="Class 9a"/><facet building="Class 9b"/><facet building="Class 9c"/><facet climate="Climate zone 8"/></meta><sptc>4.2.3</sptc><title id="_ad0e56e1-8e15-48cb-9977-550c99bfb8cc">Excavation for footings</title><archive-num>2019: 3.2.2.1</archive-num><clause-variation href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/7636_0.4.0.xml" variation="NSW" variation-type="REPLACE">NSW REPLACE Clause</clause-variation><subclause id="_a234034c-6c72-4a81-880c-6bf8dd589ac4" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_22a9e09f-316a-4760-88ae-1e6282cba0c1">SubClause</title><num>1</num><p>Excavation for footings, including thickenings for slabs and pads must be clean cut with vertical sides, wherever possible.</p></subclause><subclause id="_90882cd3-a5d1-4ed3-8eb4-2e9e65da70a8" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_3b7d06d8-d015-4457-aa01-161f8b61026e">SubClause</title><num>2</num><p>The base of the excavation must beâ€”</p><ol outputclass="alpha"><li id="_04c8633c-9ec3-443a-9795-d8495d15ca6d">for flat <xref xmlns:inv="urn:xpressauthor:xpressdocument" format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/1463_0.4.0.xml#_fb3536f6-7ee5-4a29-a4da-402a8e1168dc" id="_3152cb48-5295-4846-84a8-cac722094823" inv:access="external" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">sites</xref>, generally level but may slope not more than 1:40 to allow excavations to drain; and</li><li id="_bf411c47-0942-4e02-b3d2-fb09a07b698e">for sloping <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/1463_0.4.0.xml#_fb3536f6-7ee5-4a29-a4da-402a8e1168dc" id="_f2eb82b4-69e1-4419-a9d9-7005cb0a8203" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">sites</xref> at an angle of not more than 1:10; and</li><li id="_e950340e-c2d9-4dff-90cb-eed08cea05c8">for stepped footings in accordance with <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/1007_0.9.0.xml#_076a332b-104d-4079-9510-c6fbeb7bdf70" id="_a937e722-bd37-4d64-9bed-879b329b0cb7" scope="local" type="clause">4.2.7</xref>.</li></ol></subclause><subclause id="_8945c38f-b0a9-4158-aa0e-21ea63febfec" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_1a1949ae-f76c-4b3b-b65e-9134736b3208">SubClause</title><num>3</num><p>Footing excavations must be free of loose earth, tree roots, mud or debris.</p></subclause><subclause id="_ed670d9c-e534-4ca1-9625-3d137d03601d" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_6f65522d-7c67-4292-b79c-bcb811c66aed">SubClause</title><num>4</num><p>Topsoil containing grass roots must be removed from the <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/1463_0.4.0.xml#_fb3536f6-7ee5-4a29-a4da-402a8e1168dc" id="_9d3e2b63-874b-4772-9406-afc233100622" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">site</xref> of the <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/1315_0.7.0.xml#_8bb7272b-1ab2-45ba-9642-40b192e2393a" id="_527a0e85-bb79-45ce-a2fc-1047952a89b5" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">foundation</xref>.</p></subclause><subclause id="_86e1f564-ed7c-4773-af9e-fcfedbefd588" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_e56adf98-796e-49be-a186-071ea5aaa983">SubClause</title><num>5</num><p>Excavation depths and soil cuts must comply with <xref xmlns:inv="urn:xpressauthor:xpressdocument" format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/4177_0.6.0.xml#_cbce8ccd-222d-4370-a372-b3c3e9384f1a" id="_2a2b4310-9a20-4165-81c3-3ccbb088844e" inv:access="external" scope="local" type="part">Part 3.2</xref>.</p></subclause><subclause id="_3d38daa1-7037-4841-ab10-ee40a2d9df18" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_d2f2a5ea-622a-4a36-94c7-e1fa2adc34eb">SubClause</title><num>6</num><p>On loose sand <xref xmlns:inv="urn:xpressauthor:xpressdocument" format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/1463_0.4.0.xml#_fb3536f6-7ee5-4a29-a4da-402a8e1168dc" id="_32cc8ff6-2c77-4830-9bfe-70fd92e9d182" inv:access="external" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">sites</xref> or <xref xmlns:inv="urn:xpressauthor:xpressdocument" format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/1463_0.4.0.xml#_fb3536f6-7ee5-4a29-a4da-402a8e1168dc" id="_cbf1b2e1-bcb7-431b-8ea6-04fa5bd9a62c" inv:access="external" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">sites</xref> subject to wind or water erosion, the depth below <xref xmlns:inv="urn:xpressauthor:xpressdocument" format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/1274_0.10.0.xml#_8a0dd7f5-e2b1-4d63-8041-541e9efbf108" id="_9dbc98a2-be48-492b-88c3-1686368caa16" inv:access="external" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">finished ground level</xref> to the bottom of footings must be not less than 300 mm.</p></subclause><subclause id="_75bf109b-f8bb-4256-859e-885865ccf351" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_c40bc97c-a5a1-4301-a438-14c46f4e40a3">SubClause</title><num>7</num><p>The height of a finished slab-on-ground must be in accordance with <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/982_1.17.0.xml#_d35409cd-8e51-49cc-b148-1e2a2f2ae8ae" id="_c8a927d7-d54e-45d2-bac8-d52e43bf3f4e" scope="local" type="clause">3.3.3(b)</xref>.</p></subclause></clause>